[
    {
        "content": "<p>After I use the simp tactic, or any tactic for that matter, is there an easy way in interactive mode to view which rules were applied?</p>",
        "id": 199332877,
        "sender_full_name": "Spencer Killen",
        "timestamp": 1590980532
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <code>squeeze_simp</code> instead and it will print out a <code>simp only</code> invocation with the same result</p>",
        "id": 199332894,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1590980576
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Awesome, thanks! :)</p>",
        "id": 199332999,
        "sender_full_name": "Spencer Killen",
        "timestamp": 1590980725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There are also some trace options you can read about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/extras/simp.html\">here</a>.</p>",
        "id": 199333071,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryan Gin-ge Chen",
        "timestamp": 1590980798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Haha thanks, <code>set_option trace.simplify true</code> gave me a wonderfully huge list of failed attempts</p>",
        "id": 199333221,
        "sender_full_name": "Spencer Killen",
        "timestamp": 1590981033
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Such is the life of a simplifier.</p>",
        "id": 199333228,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1590981054
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>set_option trace.simplify.rewrite true</code> is the one you want.</p>",
        "id": 199347411,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1591000875
    }
]